ist will:</p><ul style="font-size: 14px;"><li>&#65279;<span style="font-size: 14px;float: none;">Review your medical history</span></li><li><p>Perform a physical examination</p></li><li>Review the results of any tests you have had</li><li>Discuss treatment options that require radiation therapy</li></ul><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>Who will I meet at this appointment? </b></p><p style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-size: 14px;float: none;">Your will meet your radiation oncologist and possibly a trainee in radiation oncology.</span><br/><b><br/>Where will this appointment take place? </b></p><p style="font-size: 14px;">Your appointment take place at the <span style="font-size: 14px;float: none;">Lakeshore General Hospital, 160 Stillview Ave, Pointe-Claire, H9R 2Y2. </span>The exact location of this appointment will be specified by the clerical staff when your appointment is given. <br/><span style="font-size: 14px;float: none;">Please click </span><a href="https://ciusss-ouestmtl.gouv.qc.ca/en/contact-location/general-and-specialized-care-hospitals/lakeshore-general-hospital/" target="" style="background-color: transparent;font-size: 14px;">here</a><span style="font-size: 14px;float: none;"> to access the <span style="font-size: 14px;float: none;">Lakeshore General Hospital </span>website.</span><br/><br/><b>How should I prepare for this appointment?</b></p><p style="font-size: 14px;">There is no specific preparation required for this appointment.<br/><b><br/>What should I bring to this appointment?</b></p><p style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-size: 14px;float: none;">Please bring your list of current medications, including over-the-counter medications, with you. If you\'ve had any recent tests done outside of the hospital, please bring the reports with you, if available. </span><span style="font-size: 14px;float: none;">Please bring your RAMQ card as well as your hospital card.</span><br/><b><br/>What should I expect during this appointment?</b></p><p style="font-size: 14px;">You should expect to meet with your radiation oncologist and discuss about your current symptoms, your physical health, the tests and treatments already undergone for your condition, and other tests that might be required. Tests may include:</p><ul style="font-size: 14px;"><li>Blood tests</li><li>Imaging examinations such as a CT scan or an MRI</li></ul><p style="font-size: 14px;">If treatments are necessary, your radiation-oncologist will discuss your radiotherapy treatment plan. This may include: </p><ul style="font-size: 14px;"><li><span style="font-size: 14px;float: none;">The CT scan for planning of your treatment</span></li><li>The number of treatments</li><li>The frequency of treatments</li><li>The length of each treatment</li><li>The possible start date</li><li>The preparation for treatment</li><li>The possible side effects</li></ul><p></p>', NULL, 22, 1, '#FFAB00', 1, '2022-01-21 17:58:01', 7, '2024-05-16 10:36:09', 'xd4DDbPbjj'),
