(94, 'Appointment', 1, 'Consulte en Medecine buccale oncologie', 'Consultation for Oral Medicine - Oncology', '<p style="font-size: 14px;"><br/><b>FR_ What is the purpose of this appointment?<br/></b><br/>Your oncology pathway begins with a consultation with your Medical Oncologist. During this consultation, your Medical Oncologist will:</p><ul style="font-size: 14px;"><li>Review your medical history</li><li>Perform a physical examination</li><li>Review the results of any tests you have had</li><li>Determine if treatment is necessary</li></ul><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>Who will I meet at this appointment?</b><br/><br/>You will meet your Medical Oncologist.<br/><br/><b>Where will this appointment take place?</b><br/><br/>Either on DS1 or DRC at the Cancer Centre, depending on where the Radiation Oncologist\'s clinic is located that day. When you check-in you will be provided with the exact location of your appointment.<br/><br/><b>How should I prepare for this appointment?</b><br/><br/>There is no specific preparation required for this appointment.<br/><br/><b>What should I bring to this appointment?</b><br/><br/>Please bring your list of current medications, including over-the-counter medications, with you. If you\'ve had any recent tests done outside of the hospital, please bring the reports with you, if available. Also bring your RAMQ and Hospital card.<br/><br/><b>What should I expect at this moment?</b><br/><br/>If treatment is necessary, your Medical Oncologist will explain to you your treatment plan, including the:</p><ul style="font-size: 14px;"><li>Number of treatments</li><li>Frequency of treatments</li><li>Length of each treatment</li><li>Possible start date</li><li>Preparation for treatment and possible side effects</li></ul>', '<p><br/><b>What is the purpose of this appointment?<br/></b><br/>Your oncology pathway begins with a consultation with your Medical Oncologist. During this consultation, your Medical Oncologist will:</p><ul><li>Review your med