(132, 'Appointment', 1, 'Rendez-vous de suivi avec le Dr David Fleiszer', 'Follow-up Appointment with Dr. David Fleiszer', '<p><br/></p><!--StartFragment--><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b></b></p><p><b></b></p><p><b>Quel est le but de ce rendez-vous?</b><br/></p><p style="font-size: 14px;">Ce rendez-vous est un suivi avec votre chirurgien oncologue, le Dr David Fleiszer, qui évaluera votre condition et qui pourrait discuter avec vous des sujets suivants:</p><ul style="font-size: 14px;"><li>Résultats de examens effectués et examens à effectuer dans le futur</li><li>Effets secondaires de vos traitements </li><li>Vos symptômes et votre santé actuelle</li></ul><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>Qui vais-je rencontrer lors de ce rendez-vous?</b><br/><br/><span style="font-size: 14px;float: none;">Votre chirurgien oncologue, le Dr David Fleiszer et possiblement un étudiant ou résident en chirurgie oncologique.</span></p><!--EndFragment--><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>Où aura lieu ce rendez-vous?</b><br/><br/>Votre rendez-vous aura lieu à l\'Établissement Médical Opal, Centre du cancer, bloc D, niveau RC, salle 1438 (D RC.1438). Vous devrez vous enregistrer en utilisant votre téléphone ou via les bornes placées dans la salle d\'attente, en utilisant votre carte d\'assurance maladie (RAMQ). Vous pouvez ensuite prendre place dans la salle d’attente. Vous serez averti sur votre téléphone et sur les écrans de la salle d’attente (votre prénom suivi des trois premières lettres de votre nom de famille) quand Dr Fleiszer est prêt à vous voir. </p><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>Comment dois-je me préparer pour ce rendez-vous?</b><br/><br/>Il n\'y a pas de préparation spécifique requise pour ce rendez-vous.<br/><br/><b>Que dois-je apporter à ce rendez-vous?<br/><br/></b>S\'il vous plait apportez une liste de médicaments avec vous et les résultats de test que vous auriez fait ailleur que notre hôpital. Veuillez emporter votre carte d\'assurance maladie et votre carte d\'hôpital.<br/><br/><b>À quoi dois-je m\'attendre durant ce rendez-vous?</b><br/><br/>Vous rencontrez le Dr Fleiszer afin de discuter de vos symptomes, votre santé physique et autres. Cette information permettera à votre médecin de vous donner des meilleurs soins selon votre condition physique et vos besoins. N\'hésitez pas d\'écrire les questions que vous avez pour le <span style="font-size: 14px;float: none;">Dr Fleiszer </span>et de les apporter avec vous à votre rendez-vous.</p><!--EndFragment--><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p style="font-size: 14px;"></p>', '<p><br/></p><p><b></b></p><p><b>What is the purpose of this appointment? </b><br/></p><p style="font-size: 14px;">This is a follow-up appointment with your Surgical Oncologist, Dr. David Fleiszer. During this appointment, Dr. Fleiszer will assess your condition and may discuss any of the following issues with you:</p><ul style="font-size: 14px;"><li>Test results and future tests to be ordered</li><li>Side effects of treatment </li><li>Symptoms you may be currently experiencing</li></ul><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>Who will I meet at this appointment? </b></p><p style="font-size: 14px;">You will meet Dr. David Fleiszer and possibly a trainee in surgical oncology.</p><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>Where will this appointment take place? </b><br/><br/>This appointment will take place at the Opal Medical Institution - Cancer Centre, Block D, level RC, Room 1438 (D RC.1438). You need to check-in using your phone or via the kiosks in the waiting room with your RAMQ card. You can then have a seat in the waiting room. You will be notified on your phone and on the waiting room screens (Your first name and first three letters of your last name) when it is time to see Dr. Fleiszer.</p><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>How should I prepare for this appointment? </b><br/><br/>There is no specific preparation required for this appointment.<br/><b><br/>What should I bring to this appointment? </b></p><p style="font-size: 14px;">Please bring your list of current medications, including over-the-counter medications, with you. If you\'ve had any recent tests done outside of the hospital, please bring the reports with you, if available. Please bring your RAMQ card as well as your blue Opal General Hospital card.<br/><b><br/>What should I expect during this appointment? </b><br/><br/>You should expect to meet with Dr. Fleiszer and discuss about your current symptoms, your physical health and more. This information will be used to help him better care for you and your needs. Feel free to write down any questions you may have and bring them with you to the follow-up appointment.</p><p><br/></p>', NULL, 20, 2, '#D50000', 1, '2022-01-21 17:58:01', 13, '2018-11-07 16:03:31', 'gKeATBcIa8'),
(133, 'Appointment', 1, 'Rendez-vous de suivi avec le Dr William Foulkes, généticien', 'Follow-Up Appointment with Dr. William Foulkes, Medical Geneticist', '<p>...</p>', '<p></p><p><b>What is the purpose of this appointment?<br/> </b></p><p><br/></p><p>In most cases, the purpose of the follow-up appointment is to discuss the results of any genetic testing that was offered to you at your previous visit in Medical Genetics.</p><p><br/></p><p>In some cases, a follow-up appointment may be requested by yourself or your genetics specialist as a routine “check-in” to discuss:</p><p><br/></p><p>- Your current health concerns or any changes in your health</p><p><br/></p><p>- Results of your cancer screening tests</p><p><br/></p><p>- Symptoms you may be experiencing</p><p><br/></p><p>- Genetic risk for other family members</p><p><br/></p><p><b><br/>Who will I meet at this appointment?</b></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>You will meet with Dr. William Foulkes, Medical Geneticist at the McGill University Health Centre, and possibly a trainee in Medical Genetics.</p><p><br/></p><p><b><br/>Where will this appointment take place?</b></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>Your follow-up appointment in Medical Genetics will take place at the Opal Medical Institution - Cancer Centre, Block D, Level S1, Room 1620 (D S1.1620). You need to check-in at the D S1.1620 reception. You can then have a seat in the waiting room. You will be notified on your phone and on the waiting room screens (Your first name and first three letters of your last name) when it\'s time to see Dr. William Foulkes.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><b>How should I prepare for this appointment?</b></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>There is no specific preparation required for this appointment. If you are expecting to receive test results at this appointment, you are welcome to have a support person such as a family member or friend accompany you to your appointment.</p><p><br/></p><p><b><br/>What should I bring to this appointment?</b></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p> Please bring your RAMQ card as well as your blue Opal General Hospital card.</p><p><br/></p><p><b><br/>What should I expect during this appointment?</b></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>You should expect to meet with Dr. William Foulkes, Medical Geneticist, to discuss the results of any testing that was offered to you at your first visit. If you are found to test positive for a specific genetic change (“mutation”), the meaning of this result for you and other family members will be explained in detail. Based on your test results (positive, negative, or uncertain), the genetics specialist will discuss with you the most appropriate cancer screening and/or treatment based on your level of genetic risk. This information will then be communicated to your doctor(s) so that he/she can better care for you and your specific health needs. Genetic counselling services may also be offered to your family members, if appropriate. Please feel free to write down any questions you may have and bring them with you to the</p><p><br/></p><p>follow-up appointment.</p>', NULL, 22, 2, '#D50000', 1, '2022-01-21 17:58:01', 15, '2024-05-16 10:36:09', 'TdE8shwhm0'),
