rivacy and confidentiality during this medical consultation.<br/><br/><b>How should I prepare for this appointment?</b><br/>Since you will be using your telephone, computer or mobile device, you should choose a private location that is both quiet and maintains your personal confidentiality during the consultation. <br/><br/><u>If you are having an online video conference, make sure that you:</u></p><p></p><ul><li>Feel reasonably comfortable with the technical skills needed to participate in a video chat.</li><li>Have access to the internet.</li><li>Are using a device that has both a microphone and camera.</li><li>Have read the 2 consent forms you received.</li></ul><p>Be prepared to be asked:</p><p></p><ul><li>To identify yourself (if you are not known to Dr. Pratt)</li><li>For your verbal consent to participate with Dr. Pratt by telephone or video consultation</li></ul><p><b>What should I bring to this appointment?</b><br/>Please have a list of your current medications, including over-the-counter medications, with you.<br/><br/><b>What should I expect during this appointment?</b><br/>You should expect to speak with Dr. Pratt to discuss your psychological symptoms and needs, other current symptoms, your physical health and more. This information will be used by your therapist to provide you the appropriate care. Feel free to write down any questions you may have and ask them during the appointment.<br/></p>', NULL, 27, 2, '#1B5E20', 1, '2000-01-01 00:00:00', 62, '2021-04-27 23:37:59', 'z6fnKPSnLL'),
