vous demande :</p><p></p><ul><li>De vous identifier (si vous n\'êtes pas connu du Dre Perez).</li><li>De donner votre consentement verbal pour participer à une consultation téléphonique ou en vidéo avec la Dre Perez.</li></ul><p><b>Que dois-je apporter à ce rendez-vous?</b><br/>Veuillez avoir une liste de vos médicaments, y compris les médicaments en ventre libre.<br/><br/><b>À quoi devrais-je m\'attendre durant ce rendez-vous?</b><br/>Vous devriez vous attendre à parler avec le Dr Saleh afin de discuter de vos symptômes et besoins psychologiques, d\'autres symptômes actuels, de votre santé physique et autres sujets lié à votre santé. Ces informations seront utilisées pour vous fournir les soins appropriés. N\'hésitez pas à noter toutes vos questions et à les poser lors du rendez-vous.<br/></p>', '<p><b>General Information</b><br/>Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, onsite visits to MUHC hospital clinics have been reduced or, in some cases, stopped. Instead of coming to the hospital for your visit, your nurse, doctor or other health care professional will use the telephone or the computer to perform video consultations to complement your care and to make sure that good communication continues between you and your health care team.   <br/><br/><b>What is the purpose of this appointment?</b><br/>Your psychology pathway begins with a consultation with Dr. Perez. This consultation will be performed via phone call or videoconference. During this consultation, Dr. Perez will:</p><p></p><ul><li>Review your psychological history</li><li>Review the result of the distress screening </li><li>Provide support and educational material if needed</li></ul><p></p><p><b>Who will I meet at this appointment? </b><br/>Your will speak with Dr. Perez. <br/><br/><b>Where will this appointment take place? </b><br/>This appointment will take place at in the location of your choice, usually in your home. It is advised that you choose an environment that maintains your privacy and confidentiality during this medical consultation.<br/><br/><b>How should I prepare for this appointment?</b><br/>Since you will be using your telephone, computer or mobile device, you should choose a private location that is both quiet and maintains your personal confidentiality during the consultation. <br/><br/><u>If you are having an online video conference, make sure that you:</u></p><ul><li>Feel reasonably comfortable with the technical skills needed to participate in a video chat.</li><li>Have access to the internet.</li><li>Are using a device that has both a microphone and camera.</li><li>Have read the 2 consent forms you received.</li></ul><p><span>Be prepare</span></p><p><span>d to be asked:</span></p><div><span></span><ul><li>To identify yourself (if you are not known to Dr. Perez)</li><li>For your verbal consent to participate with Dr. Perez by telephone or video consultation</li></ul><div><div><b>What should I bring to this appointment?</b><br/><span>Please have a list of your current medications, including over-the-counter medications, with you.</span><br/><br/><b>What should I expect during this appointment?</b><br/><span>You should expect to speak with Dr. Perez to discuss your psychological symptoms and needs, other current symptoms, your physical health and more. This information will be used by your therapist to provide you the appropriate care. Feel free to write down any questions you may have and ask them during the appointment.</span><br/></div></div></div>', NULL, 27, 2, '#1B5E20', 1, '2000-01-01 00:00:00', 62, '2021-04-28 13:55:29', 'Mhgqf2PCCi'),
