 usually in your home. It is advised that you choose a quite environment that maintains your privacy and confidentiality during the consultation.<br/><br/><b><span id="selectionBoundary_1616112247616_30005211043484614" class="rangySelectionBoundary">&#65279;</span>How should I prepare for this appointment?<span id="selectionBoundary_1616112247616_45332838431342126" class="rangySelectionBoundary">&#65279;</span></b></p><p>Since you will be using your smart phone, tablet or computer, you should choose a private location that is both quiet and maintains your personal confidentiality during the consultation.</p><p>You are having an online video call, make sure that you:</p><ul><li>Feel reasonably comfortable with the technical skills needed to participate in a video chat.</li><li>Have access to the internet.</li><li>Are using a device that has both a microphone and camera.</li></ul><p>Be prepared to be asked:</p><ul><li>To identify yourself with personal questions and showing your ID to the camera.</li><li>For your verbal consent to participate with a remote consultation.</li></ul><p><b>What should I bring to this appointment?</b></p><p>Please have a list of your current medications, including over-the-counter medications. Also please have your RAMQ card ready in case of video call</p><p><b>What should I expect during this appointment?</b></p><p>You should expect to consult about your pain and your others symptoms with the team of clinicians at the supportive and palliative care clinic.<br/></p>', NULL, 27, 2, '#1B5E20', 1, '2000-01-01 00:00:00', 62, '2021-04-27 17:26:35', 'YRYzf0Hf6B'),
