es actuels, de votre santé physique, etc. N\'hésitez pas à noter toutes vos questions et à les poser pendant le rendez-vous.</p></div></div>', '<p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>What is the purpose of this appointment?</b></p><p style="font-size: 14px;">Your follow-up appointment in the supportive and palliative care clinic begins with Dr. Dejong. During this consultation, Dr. Dejong will:</p><ul style="font-size: 14px;"><li>Review your medical history</li><li>Perform a physical examination, if required</li><li>Review the results of any tests you have had</li><li>Assess your level pain and other symptoms</li><li>Provide support</li><li>Discuss your illness, goals of care and advanced care planning, if appropriate</li></ul><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>Who will I meet at this appointment?</b></p><p style="font-size: 14px;">You will meet Dr. Dejong and the nurse of the team</p><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>Where will this appointment take place?</b></p><p style="font-size: 14px;">Opal Medical Institution - Cancer Centre, Block D, Level 2, Room D02.9005 You need to check-in with the clerk at the D02.9005 reception. You can then have a seat in the waiting. You will be call when it is time to see your physician and nurse.</p><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>How should I prepare for this appointment?</b></p><p style="font-size: 14px;">There is no specific preparation required for this appointment.</p><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>What should I bring to this appointment?</b></p><p style="font-size: 14px;">Please bring your list of current medications, including over-the-counter medications, with you. If you\'ve had any recent tests done outside of the hospital, please bring the reports with you, if available. Please bring your RAMQ card as well as your Opal General Hospital card.</p><p style="font-size: 14px;"><b>What should I expect during this appointment?</b></p><p style="font-size: 14px;">You should expect to meet with Dr. Dejong to discuss your current symptoms, your physical health, and more. Feel free to write down any questions you may have and ask them during the appointment.</p>', NULL, 30, 2, '#1B5E20', 1, '2000-01-01 00:00:00', 63, '2021-03-19 16:18:21', 'TdNpNsj7jW'),
