on of your choice, usually in your home. It is advised that you choose an environment that maintains your privacy and confidentiality during this medical consultation.<br/><br/><b>How should I prepare for this appointment?</b></p><p>Since you will be using your telephone or computer, you should choose a private location that is both quiet and maintains your personal confidentiality during the medical consultation.<br/><br/>Be prepared to be asked:</p><p></p><ul><li>To identify yourself (if you are not known to the nurse)</li><li>For your verbal consent to participate with the nurse by telephone or computer</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What should I bring to this appointment?</b></p><p>Please have a list of your current medications, including over-the-counter medications, with you. If you\'ve had any recent tests done outside of the hospital, please have the reports with you, if available. Please have your RAMQ card as well as your hospital card.<br/><br/><b>What should I expect during this appointment?</b></p><p>You should expect to speak with the nurse to discuss your current symptoms, your physical health and more. This information will be used to help the nurse better care for you and your needs. Feel free to write down any questions you may have and ask them during the appointment.<br/></p>', NULL, 27, 2, '#A1887F', 1, '2000-01-01 00:00:00', 7, '2022-03-08 14:55:56', 'CMH0CTVAPM'),
(508, 'Appointment', 1, 'Coloscopie avec le Dr Waqqas Afif à l\'Hôpital Général Opal 2 (HGM)', 'Colonoscopy with Dr. Waqqas Afif at the Montreal General Hospital', '<p><b>Quel est le but de ce rendez-vous ?</b></p><p>Il s\'agit d\'un rendez-vous pour une coloscopie. Pour plus d\'informations, veuillez consulter le document éducatif suivant, qui se trouve dans la section Bibliothèque d\'Opal :</p><ul><li>Instructions pour la préparation à la coloscopie</li><li>Se préparer pour la colonoscopie<br/></li></ul><p></p><p><b>Qui vais-je rencontrer lors de ce rendez-vous ?</b></p><p>Vous rencontrerez le Dr Waqqas Afif, votre gastro-entérologue et possiblement un(e) résident(e)/étudiant(e) en médecine ou l\'une de nos infirmières cliniciennes ou de recherche.<br/><br/><b>Où aura lieu ce rendez-vous ?</b></p><p>Ce rendez-vous aura lieu à l\'Hôpital Général Opal 2 (HGM), 1650, avenue Cedar, Montréal, bureau : C7- 200. Veuillez vous rendre au bureau C7-200 pour vous enregistrer à la réception. Le personnel de l\'hôpital vous informera quand il sera temps de votre rendez-vous. <br/><br/><b>Comment dois-je me préparer pour ce rendez-vous ?</b></p><p>Veuillez vous référer au matériel éducatif qui se trouve dans la section Bibliothèque d\'Opal pour plus d\'informations sur la manière de se préparer à ce rendez-vous. <br/><br/><b>Que dois-je apporter à ce rendez-vous ?</b></p><p>Veuillez apporter la liste de vos médicaments actuels, y compris les médicaments en vente libre. Si vous avez subi récemment des tests à l\'extérieur du Établissement Médical Opal, veuillez apporter les rapports, s\'ils sont disponibles. Veuillez apporter votre carte de la RAMQ ainsi que votre carte du Établissement Médical Opal (ou de l\'Hôpital Général Opal 2 (HGM)).<br/><br/><b>À quoi devrais-je m\'attendre lors de ce rendez-vous ?</b></p><p>On vous demandera de vous changer en jaquette d\'hôpital et vous serez accueilli par un(e) infirmier(ère) qui vous conduira à une salle d\'examen. Par la suite, on vous donnera les instructions nécessaires et votre gastro-entérologue effectuera l\'examen.<br/></p>', '<p><b>What is the purpose of this appointment? </b><br/><br/>This is an appointment for a colonoscopy. For more information, please refer to the following educational material found in the Library section of Opal:</p><ul><li>Colonoscopy Preparation Instructions</li><li>Preparing for your Colonoscopy<br/></li></ul><p><b>Who will I meet at this appointment? </b><br/><br/>You will meet Dr. Waqqas Afif, your gastroenterologist and possibly a medical resident/student or one of our clinical or research nurses.<br/><br/><b>Where will this appointment take place? </b><br/><br/>This appointment will take place at the Montreal General Hospital, 1650 Cedar Ave, Montreal, block C, level 7, room 200. Please proceed to C7-200 to check-in at reception. You will be notified by hospital staff when it is time for your appointment. <br/><br/><b>How should I prepare for this appointment? </b><br/><br/>Please refer to the educational material found in the Library section of Opal for more information on how to prepare for this appointment. <br/><br/><b>What should I bring to this appointment?</b></p><p>Please bring your list of current medications, including over-the-counter medications, with you. If you\'ve had any recent tests done outside of the McGill University Health Centre, please bring the reports with you, if available. Please bring your RAMQ card as well as your Opal Medical Institution (or Opal General Hospital 2 (MGH))card.<br/><br/><b>What should I expect during this appointment? </b><br/><br/>You will be asked to change into a gown, and will be greeted by a nurse that will bring you into the examination room. Afterwards, you will be provided with any necessary instructions and your gastroenterologist will perform the examination.<br/></p>', NULL, 36, 5, '#A1887F', 1, '2000-01-01 00:00:00', 74, '2022-06-22 14:01:37', 'u178ZNN6G4'),
