i par un(e) infirmier(ère) qui vous conduira à une salle d\'examen. Par la suite, on vous donnera les instructions nécessaires et votre gastro-entérologue effectuera l\'examen.<br/></p>', '<p><b>What is the purpose of this appointment? </b><br/><br/>This is an appointment for a colonoscopy. For more information, please refer to the following educational material found in the Library section of Opal:</p><ul><li>Colonoscopy Preparation Instructions</li><li>Preparing for your Colonoscopy<br/></li></ul><p><b>Who will I meet at this appointment? </b><br/><br/>You will meet Dr. Peter Lakatos, your gastroenterologist, and possibly a medical resident/student or one of our clinical or research nurses.<br/><br/><b>Where will this appointment take place? </b><br/><br/>This appointment will take place at the Montreal General Hospital, 1650 Cedar Ave, Montreal, block C, level 7, room 200. Please proceed to C7-200 to check-in at reception. You will be notified by hospital staff when it is time for your appointment.    <br/><br/><b>How should I prepare for this appointment? </b><br/><br/>Please refer to the educational material found in the Library section of Opal for more information on how to prepare for this appointment. <br/><br/><b>What should I bring to this appointment? </b><br/><br/>Please bring your list of current medications, including over-the-counter medications, with you. If you\'ve had any recent tests done outside of the McGill University Health Centre, please bring the reports with you, if available. Please bring your RAMQ card as well as your Opal Medical Institution (or Opal General Hospital 2 (MGH))card.<br/><br/><b>What should I expect during this appointment? </b><br/><br/>You will be asked to change into a gown, and will be greeted by a nurse that will bring you into the examination room. Afterwards, you will be provided with any necessary instructions and your gastroenterologist will perform the examination.<br/></p>', NULL, 36, 5, '#A1887F', 1, '2000-01-01