sis or your treatment</li></ul><p><br/></p><p><b>Who will I meet at this appointment?</b></p><p><span>You will meet<span style="font-size: 14px;float: none;">Dr. Raghu Rajan</span>, and possibly a trainee in medical oncology.</span></p><p><b>Where will this appointment take place?</b></p><p>This appointment will take place in the location of your choice, usually in your home. It is advised that you choose an environment that maintains your privacy and confidentiality during this medical consultation.</p><p><b>How should I prepare for this appointment?</b></p><p>Since you will be using your telephone, you should choose a private location that is both quiet and maintains your personal confidentiality during the medical consultation.</p><p>Be prepared to be asked:</p><ul><li>To identify yourself (if you are not known to <span style="font-size: 14px;float: none;">Dr. Raghu Rajan</span>)</li><li>For your verbal consent to participate with the doctor by telephone</li></ul><p><b>What should I bring to this appointment?</b></p><p>Please have a list of your current medications, including over-the-counter medications, with you. If you\'ve had any recent tests done outside of the hospital, please have the reports with you, if available. Please have your RAMQ card as well as your hospital card.</p><p><b>What should I expect during this appointment?</b></p><p>You should expect to meet with Dr. Raghu Rajan to discuss your current symptoms, your physical health, the tests, and treatments already undergone for your condition, and other tests that might be required. Tests may include:</p><ul><li>Blood tests</li><li>Imaging examinations such as a CT scan or an MRI</li></ul><p>If treatment is necessary, your doctor may discuss your treatment plan. This may include:</p><p></p><ul><li>The type of medications you need and their possible side effects</li><li>A tentative start date</li><li>The duration of treatment</li><li>Preparation necessary for the treatment</li></ul><p></p>', NULL, 27, 2, '#8D6E63', 1, '2000-01-01 00:00:00', 62, '2023-03-06 12:20:00', 'n8OxwH5xUV'),
(605, 'Appointment', 1, 'Rendez-vous de suivi avec le Dr Sanchez-Salas', 'Follow-up Appointment with Dr. Sanchez-Salas', '<p><b>Quel est le but de ce rendez-vous?</b><br/><br/>Ce rendez-vous est un suivi avec votre oncologue urologue, le Dr Sanchez-Salas, qui évaluera votre condition et qui pourrait discuter avec vous des sujets suivants:</p><ul><li>Résultats d\'examens effectués et examens à effectuer dans le futur</li><li>Effets secondaires de vos traitements</li><li>Vos symptômes et votre santé actuelle</li><li>Il répondra à toutes les questions ou préoccupations que vous avez concernant votre état de santé</li></ul><p><b>Qui vais-je rencontrer lors de ce rendez-vous?</b><br/><br/>Votre oncologue urologue, Dr Sanchez-Salas et possiblement un étudiant ou résident en oncologie urologique.<br/><br/><b>Où aura lieu ce rendez-vous?</b><br/><br/>Votre rendez-vous aura lieu à l\'Établissement Médical Opal, Centre du cancer, bloc D, niveau RC, salle 1438 (D RC.1438). Vous devrez vous enregistrer en utilisant votre téléphone ou via les bornes placées dans la salle d\'attente, en utilisant votre carte d\'assurance maladie (RAMQ). Vous pouvez ensuite prendre place dans la salle d’attente. Vous serez averti sur votre téléphone et sur les écrans de la salle d’attente (votre prénom suivi des trois premières lettres de votre nom de famille) quand Dr Sanchez-Salas est prêt à vous voir.<br/><br/><b>Comment dois-je me préparer pour ce rendez-vous?</b><br/><br/>Il n\'y a pas de préparation spécifique requise pour ce rendez-vous.<br/><br/><b>Que dois-je apporter à ce rendez-vous?</b><br/><br/>S\'il vous plait apportez une liste de médicaments avec vous et les résultats de test que vous auriez fait ailleur que notre hôpital. Veuillez emporter votre carte d\'assurance maladie et votre carte d\'hôpital.<br/><br/><b>À quoi dois-je m\'attendre durant ce rendez-vous?</b><br/><br/>Vous rencontrez le Dr Sanchez-Salas afin de discuter de vos symptomes, votre santé physique et autres. Cette information permettera à votre médecin de vous donner des meilleurs soins selon votre condition physique et vos besoins. N\'hésitez pas d\'écrire les questions que vous avez pour le Dr Sanchez-Salas et de l\'emporter avec vous à votre rendez-vous.<br/></p>', '<p><b>What is the purpose of this appointment?</b></p><p>This is a follow-up appointment with your Urologic Oncologist, Dr. Sanchez-Salas. During this appointment, Dr. Sanchez-Salas will assess your condition and may discuss any of the following issues with you:</p><ul><li>Test results and future tests to be ordered</li><li>Side effects of treatment</li><li>Symptoms you may be currently experiencing</li><li>Answer any questions or concerns you have about your condition</li></ul><p><b>Who will I meet at this appointment?</b><br/><br/>You will meet Dr. Sanches-Salas and possibly a trainee in urological oncology.<br/><br/><b>Where will this appointment take place?</b><br/><br/>This appointment will take place at the Opal Medical Institution - Cancer Centre, Block D, level RC, Room 1438 (D RC.1438). You need to check-in using your phone or via the kiosks in the waiting room with your RAMQ card. You can then have a seat in the waiting room. You will be notified on your phone and on the waiting room screens (Your first name and first three letters of your last name) when it is time to see Dr. Sanchez-Salas.<br/><br/><b>How should I prepare for this appointment?</b><br/><br/>There is no specific preparation required for this appointment.<br/><br/><b>What should I bring to this appointment?</b><br/><br/>Please bring your list of current medications, including over-the-counter medications, with you. If you\'ve had any recent tests done outside of the hospital, please bring the reports with you, if available. Please bring your RAMQ card as well as your blue Opal General Hospital card.<br/><br/><b>What should I expect during this appointment?</b><br/><br/>You should expect to meet with Dr. Sanchez-Salas and discuss about your current symptoms, your physical health and more. This information will be used to help him better care for you and your needs. Feel free to write down any questions you may have and bring them with you to the follow-up appointment.<br/></p>', NULL, 20, 2, '#8D6E63', 1, '2000-01-01 00:00:00', 62, '2023-09-05 15:15:32', 'zMvkznq9ji'),
